      "kind": "tzx-format-query",
      "note": "`.tzx` tape image (file-formats.md FMT-TZX-*, pinned TZX v1.20): a 10-byte header (\"ZXTape!\" 1A major minor) followed by typed blocks, each introduced by a 1-byte ID. Every multi-byte field is little-endian; the 0x11/0x14 data length is a 3-byte LE value, the 0x10 length is a 2-byte WORD. This well-formed 87-byte file exercises all nine modeled block IDs in order: 0x30 text, 0x10 standard data, 0x21 group start, 0x12 pure tone, 0x13 pulse sequence, 0x11 turbo data (3-byte length), 0x14 pure data (3-byte length), 0x20 pause, 0x22 group end. The runner parses `file` (the on-disk authority) and independently serializes `tzx`; serializeMatchesFile pins serialize against the hand-authored bytes; the serialize-byte cases at offsets 24/25 (0x10 WORD length) and 63-65 / 78-80 (0x11/0x14 3-byte length) pin the length-field widths.",
